back down and try again.

253
00:16:45.212 --> 00:16:47.601
l think it's really stuck now.

254
00:16:49.172 --> 00:16:52.562
-l can't believe that didn't work.
-l know. Me neither.

255
00:16:52.812 --> 00:16:54.370
l mean. you had a sketch.

256
00:16:56.372 --> 00:16:58.727
What did you mean when
you said ''pivot''?

257
00:17:04.652 --> 00:17:07.120
How's it going?
Make any new friends?

258
00:17:07.332 --> 00:17:09.288
Yeah.
l met this woman.

259
00:17:11.772 --> 00:17:13.330
What's she like?

260
00:17:13.532 --> 00:17:15.011
Well. she's. . .

261
00:17:15.252 --> 00:17:16.526
. . .really good in bed.

262
00:17:18.252 --> 00:17:22.370
-You were going to be friends first.
-Hey. it's all your fault.

263
00:17:22.572 --> 00:17:23.368
Why?

264
00:17:23.572 --> 00:17:26.530
You didn't give me advice.
You gave me a pickup line.

265
00:17:26.732 --> 00:17:30.361
l told her l wanted to
''build a foundation and be friends. ''

266
00:17:30.612 --> 00:17:35.208
Suddenly. through no fault of my own.
l became irresistible to her!

267
00:17:36.212 --> 00:17:37.406
And her roommate!

268
00:17:39.572 --> 00:17:41.164
What about the ''closeness''?

269
00:17:41.652 --> 00:17:45.770
Closeness. schmosness! There was
three of us. for crying out loud!

270
00:17:50.252 --> 00:17:51.765
Who wants pizza?

271
00:17:52.012 --> 00:17:53.365
l do! l do! l do!

272
00:17:54.052 --> 00:17:57.761
This is great! Can you believe
l found it on the second floor?

273
00:18:00.612 --> 00:18:02.443
-Who is it?
-NYPD.

274
00:18:02.772 --> 00:18:03.682
Oh. my God!

275
00:18:05.052 --> 00:18:06.610
Just a minute. officer!

276
00:18:16.012 --> 00:18:20.164
-l'm looking for Phoebe Buffay.
-My God. it's him! lt's that cop!

277
00:18:20.372 --> 00:18:24.126
-l can't believe he found me!
-Are you going to go to jail?

278
00:18:24.652 --> 00:18:27.371
lf l go down.
you guys go down with me.

279
00:18:29.412 --> 00:18:32.768
Harboring a fugitive?
That's one-to-three years minimum.

280
00:18:33.132 --> 00:18:34.963
Good luck. Chandler.

281
00:18:38.252 --> 00:18:42.006
Arrest me. but you'll never
make it stick and you know it.

282
00:18:42.252 --> 00:18:45.403
l have no choice. it's my job.
You understand. right?

283
00:18:45.652 --> 00:18:48.371
And you understand that
l'm calling my lawyer.

284
00:18:48.572 --> 00:18:52.247
And once he puts you on the stand
he'll make you look like a fool!

285
00:18:54.052 --> 00:18:55.849
l don't like looking foolish.

286
00:18:56.372 --> 00:19:00.285
Maybe l don't arrest you today.
Maybe l came by and you weren't here.

287
00:19:00.572 --> 00:19:02.608
l'd love it if l weren't here!

288
00:19:03.332 --> 00:19:07.211
Since you're not going to jail tonight.
l was wondering if you'd. . .

289
00:19:07.452 --> 00:19:09.568
. . .like to go to dinner with me?

290
00:19:10.252 --> 00:19:11.207
Me?

291
00:19:11.612 --> 00:19:15.287
Ever since you flashed my badge.
l can't stop thinking about you.

292
00:19:15.532 --> 00:19:19.161
You're the prettiest fake
undercover whore l've ever seen.

293
00:19:20.732 --> 00:19:21.881
Nice.

294
00:19:24.572 --> 00:19:27.882
Wow. l didn't see that coming.
You're asking me out.

295
00:19:28.092 --> 00:19:31.368
l could've done it better.
but they're staring at me.

296
00:19:32.212 --> 00:19:35.522
l'd like to go out
with you. officer.

297
00:19:36.412 --> 00:19:38.084
-Gary.
-Gary.

298
00:19:38.332 --> 00:19:40.163
Okay. so it's a date.

299
00:19:40.372 --> 00:19:42.886
l got to ask you. though.
How'd you find me?

300
00:19:43.132 --> 00:19:45.930
l ran your fingerprints
through the computer.

301
00:19:46.132 --> 00:19:48.771
This was listed
as your last known address.

302
00:19:48.972 --> 00:19:49.961
lmpressive.

303
00:19:50.172 --> 00:19:54.324
Not as impressive as you. Your record
shows you've done some weird stuff.

304
00:19:55.052 --> 00:19:56.087
We'll talk at dinner.

305
00:19:57.732 --> 00:20:01.168
-So l'll come by and pick you up?
-l can't wait.

306
00:20:01.412 --> 00:20:04.165
Don't worry. l won't just
take you out for doughnuts.

307
00:20:07.372 --> 00:20:08.691
He has a gun!

308
00:20:14.972 --> 00:20:18.442
l'd like to return this couch.
l'm not satisfied with it.

309
00:20:23.132 --> 00:20:25.566
You want to return this couch?

310
00:20:26.972 --> 00:20:28.724
lt's cut in half.

311
00:20:30.372 --> 00:20:34.445
-That's what l'm telling you.
-Did you cut this couch in half?

312
00:20:35.772 --> 00:20:38.923
This couch is cut in half!

313
00:20:40.132 --> 00:20:44.091
l would like to exchange it for one
that is not cut in half.

314
00:20:45.172 --> 00:20:48.562
You're saying this couch was
delivered to you like this?

315
00:20:48.772 --> 00:20:50.763
Look. l'm a reasonable man.

316
00:20:51.012 --> 00:20:53.401
l will accept store credit.

317
00:20:54.732 --> 00:20:58.566
l'll give you store credit
in the amount of four dollars.

318
00:21:01.972 --> 00:21:03.405
l will take it.
